<cell><p>1. Find an odd natural number x such that LCM (x, 40) = 1400.</p>
<p>2. There are between 50 and 60 number of eggs in a basket. When Loza counts by 3’s, there are 2 eggs left over. When she counts by 5’s, there are 4 left over. How many eggs are there in the basket?</p>
<p>3. The GCF of two numbers is 3 and their LCM is 180. If one of the numbers is 45, then find the second number.</p>
