<li><p>If <m>f</m> is a real function defined by <m>f(x) = \frac{x - 1}{x + 1}</m>. Show that <m>f(2x) = \frac{3f(x) + 1}{f(x) + 3}</m>.</p></li>
<li><p>Find two functions <m>f</m> and <m>g</m> so that the given function <m>h(x) = (f \circ g)(x)</m>, where</p></li>
</ol>
