<p>Therefore, <m>p(r) = R</m>.</p>
<p>The result we just proved is called the remainder theorem.</p>
<table>
<tabular>
<row header="yes">
<cell><alert>The Remainder Theorem</alert></cell>
</row>

<row>
<cell>When a polynomial <m>p(x)</m> of degree at least 1 is divided by <m>x - r</m>, then the remainder is <m>p(r)</m>.</cell>
</row>
