<p>In the previous subsection we noted that the exponential function <m>f(x) = b^{x}</m> (where <m>b &gt; 0</m> and <m>b \neq 1</m>) is one to one. Thus, the exponential function has an inverse function. What is the inverse of <m>f(x) = b^{x}</m>?</p>
