<p>(ii) <em><alert>l</alert></em><sub>1</sub> and <em><alert>l</alert></em><sub>2</sub> are perpendicular, denoted by <em><alert>l</alert></em><sub>1</sub>⊥ <em><alert>l</alert></em><sub>2</sub> , iff <em>m</em><sub>1</sub><em>m</em><sub>2</sub>= −1 (or )</p>

<p>Moreover, if <alert><em>l</em><sub>1</sub></alert> and <alert><em>l</em><sub>2</sub></alert> are both vertical lines then they are parallel. However, if one of them is horizontal and the other is vertical, then they are perpendicular.</p>
