<p><alert>(II)</alert> <alert>Equation of shifted hyperbolas:</alert></p>
<p>The center of a horizontal or vertical hyperbola may be not at origin but at some other point C(<em>h,k</em>) as shown in Figure 4.27. In this case, we form the equation of the hyperbolas by using the translation of the <em>xy</em>-coordinate system that shifts its origin to the point C(<em>h</em>, <em>k</em>). As discussed in Section 4.4, the effect of this translation is just replacing <em>x</em> and <em>y</em> by <em>x</em>−<em>h</em> and <em>y</em>−<em>k</em>, respectively, in the equation of the desired hyperbola.</p>
